The current proze in the Reference Manual is still mostly the same as it was for the legacy documentation (from libcwd version 1.x). All documentation related to Memory Allocation Debugging was removed (as memory allocation debugging was removed from libcwd). See NEWS for more changes from version 1 -> 2. The remaining documentation needs reviewing and maybe even rewrites in parts to become up-to-date and well fitting for modern documentation of a C++ library.
